==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mental
<hw>Men"tal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>mentum</ets>
the chin.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the chin;
genian; <as>as, the <ex>mental</ex> nerve; the <ex>mental</ex>
region.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mental</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Mental
<hw>Men"tal</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A plate or scale
covering the mentum or chin of a fish or reptile.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mental</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Mental
<hw>Men"tal</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. L. <ets>mentalis</ets>,
fr. <ets>mens</ets>, <ets>mentis</ets>, the mind; akin to E.
<ets>mind</ets>. See <er>Mind</er>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to the
mind; intellectual; <as>as, <ex>mental</ex> faculties; <ex>mental</ex>
operations, conditions, or exercise.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What a <qex>mental</qex> power⟦br⟧
This eye shoots forth!</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Mental alienation</b></col>, <cd>insanity.</cd> --
<col><b>Mental arithmetic</b></col>, <cd>the art or practice of solving
arithmetical problems by mental processes, unassisted by written
figures.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>mentalism</ent>⟦br⟧
